\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Absent - Mild - Moderate - Severe}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 1 Intense fear of Abandonment, even going to intense measures to avoid real or imagined seperation or rejection}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -mild}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 2 A pattern of unstable intense relationships, such as idealizing someone one moment and then usddenly believing the person doesn't care enough or is cruel}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -moderate}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 3 Rapid changes in self-identity and self-image that include shifting goals and values, and seeing yourself as bad or as if you don't exist at all. "If I'm not in a relationship, or I'm not being heard, or if I'm not being recognized, then I don't exist. I'm invisible.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -absent(???); don't see myself as bad or nonexistant. With katherine i find myself shifting goals. Outside of that, it would be absent.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 4 Periods of stress-related paranoia and loss of contact with reality, lasting from a few minutes to a few hours.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -absent(???)}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 5 Impulsive and risky behavior, such as gambling, reckless driving, unsafe sex, spending sprees, binge eating or drug abuse, or sabotaging success by suddenly quitting a good job or ending a positive relationship.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -absent (mild in the past i think???)}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 6 suicidal threats or behavior or self injury}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -absent}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 7 Wide mood swings lasting from a few hours to a few days, which can include intense happiness, irritability, shame, or anxiety}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -mild to moderate}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 8 Ongoing feelings  of emptiness}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -absent}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 9 Inappropriate intense anger, such as losing temper, being sarcastic or bitter, or having physical fights}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -verrrry mild}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Relationship with a BPD man}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Stage 1:  Idealization}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -greatest romance}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Stage 2: Fear of Abandonment and enmeshment.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab - just as you are starting to feel like hes the best thing that has ever happened to you, things start to change. His insecurities and fears start to crop up. He starts needing a lot of reassurance from you. He wants to know if you really love him, why you love him, maybe suggests that you\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d be better off with someone else. You reassure him, you tell him how amazing he his, how much you love him, but this doesn\u8217\'92t satisfy him for long. He\u8217\'92s getting more and more clingy, more and more needy, getting upset anytime you spend time with anyone else, doing anything else, even if its just going to work. Also expresses fears of commitment and engulfment. So its, \u8220\'93please never leave,\u8221\'94 but also, \u8220\'93I need a lot of space.\u8221\'94 When he gets to this point, he might break up with you, or just run off without saying anything. Just days ago, he was all over you, needing your reassurance, and now he\u8217\'92s out. So you are going through an emotional crash, as he withdraws his love and attention in one fell swoop. On his side, as the love addiction started to wear off, he went back into an emotionally disregulated and hyper-aroused state, vacillating between fear of abandonment, and fear of losing his independence. He associates these negative emotions and intrusive thoughts to you, where you were once his everything just last week, now he sees you as a source of his emotional suffering, and in order to escape this emotional pain, he needs to escape you.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Stage 3: Splitting}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab - he comes back and says he was scared and feeling vulnerable. He may speak of past traumas and attachment issues. He\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s sweet and idealizing you again. Then something sets him off. Maybe you mention a male coworker, or express something you dont like about him. He gets angry, starts making false characterizations, attacking you with the most hateful words. Where you were once the most perfect person on the planet, now you are the devil. In his mind, you betrayed him, you hurt him, you tried to reason with him, but he is off into another orbit. This is an up and down push pull; you\u8217\'92re the greatest thing that\u8217\'92s ever happened to him, you\u8217\'92re the worst. Argumentative, irritable, angry.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Stage 4: Paranoia and disassoication}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab -jealous, starts monitoring you, questioning your comments and motivations. Suspicious despite you are doing absolutely nothing wrong. He\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s getting more distant and deatched, not only from you, but from reality. He may be using more substances, numbing out, spacing out, basing his own actions on his delusional thinking. False idea you\u8217\'92re cheating, so he starts cheating. You are fighting almost constantly over trivial things. This intense fighting leads to a breakup.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Stage 5: The Makeup stage}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab - he goes off, realizes he can\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t live without you, begging at your feet, threatens self harm, emotionally blackmail you. You take him back, you make up, but you feel uneasy.  Mood swings from needy to angry to withdrawn, all of this keeps cycling. Leads to end of the relationship. No matter how hard you try, you can\u8217\'92t stabilize him.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Stage 7: The emotional discard.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \tab - he enters an emotional stage where he cant live with you, but cant live without you. He sees you as an oppressor. He blames and resents you for holding him back, trying to control him, and he will punish you in many ways. It is highly likely his behavior is extremely shameful.}
